    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle, then heat a separate large, wide-based pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>sliced leek</strong> with a splash of <strong>water</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, combine 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with<strong> </strong>100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>and your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> – this is your<strong> milk stock</strong></p>",
