    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and leek has softened, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>milk stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>soup base</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
